  "articleSummary": "The article argues that modern developer laptops are \"credential cruise ships\" where a single malicious click can compromise everything, making \"be careful\" an insufficient defense. It proposes a defense-in-depth strategy focused on limiting blast radius: isolate risky work using Dev Containers (mounting only the repo, not home directories), plant canary tokens as tripwires in sensitive files, delay package updates with pnpm's `minimumReleaseAge` setting to avoid the riskiest window, and rotate credentials swiftly after a breach. The tone is instructional and urgent, blending analysis of real attack vectors (prompt injection, supply-chain malware) with concrete, opinionated recommendations. The intended audience is developers and security engineers seeking practical, implementable controls rather than abstract advice.",
